Start by applying Growth Serum to a single basic ingredient to make it 'grown' (e.g., kangaroo -> grown kangaroo, value ~10-15). Concurrently, combine two other basic ingredients to create a simple hybrid (e.g., bee + snake -> flying snakebee, value ~5). The most potent step is then to combine your 'grown' ingredient with your simple hybrid. This new item will have a good positive value (e.g., 15-25). Crucially, apply the Growth Serum *once more* to this complex, combined item. This often yields the highest values (up to 35). Beware of the Mutation Catalyst, which consistently leads to negative values, and avoid applying Growth Serum multiple times to an already 'super-grown' item, as it tends to decrease value rapidly. Also, avoid combining too many complex or negative-value items, as this often results in extremely low scores.

Use 'growth serum' on individual ingredients too, as they also gain value. Be very cautious with the 'mutation catalyst'; it often reduces positive item values or creates highly negative 'overcomplicated' items. Only consider using the 'mutation catalyst' on a heavily negative item as a last resort, as it can sometimes make it slightly less negative, but it's very risky. Prioritize 'growth serum' on combined items to reach the highest values.
